The paper deals with the problem of multiple hypothesis testing, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between error probabilities, which is a common theme in statistical inference (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper mentions the special case of discrete memoryless sources, which is a topic in information theory and communication (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses geometric interpretations of the optimal decision schemes, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
